result.execSummary:
Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Clerk: Amy. 
Called:  9:15 a.m. 
INCLUDES 21CF454, 22CF185. 
State appears by ADA Molly Lawrence for ADA Zibolski. 
Defendant appears in person with Atty Jessica Phelps. 

Date and time set for waiver of prelim and plea/sentencing.  

WAIVER OF PRELIM>>
COURT questions deft as to waiver.
COURT finds waiver freely and voluntarily made.
COURT finds PC - Defendant bound over for arraignment & trial. 
Information e-filed. 

PLEA/SENTENCING>>
Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights filed.
COURT advises defendant of rights (including constitutional rights) & penalties & questions defendant to understanding.

22CF185>>State moves to DRI Count 1 (Possession of Methamphetamine) and Count 2 (Possess Drug Paraphernalia); COURT GRANTS.

PLEA: 

21CF454>>
Count 1 (Possession of Methamphetamine): GUILTY. 
Count 2 (Possess Drug Paraphernalia): GUILTY.  

COURT finds plea & waiver of rights freely & voluntary made, a factual basis & defendant guilty.

COURT w/holds finding and entry of guilt on Count 1.  COURT adopts written deferred entry of judgment agreement as signed by all parties and submitted to COURT.
COURT defers Count 1 for a period of 1 year for defendant to comply with all terms and conditions of written DEJ agreement.
If defendant is in full compliance with all terms and conditions of written DEOJ agreement within that time frame and obtains no new criminal charges, State to DISMISS Count 1.  

COURT ORDERS on Count 2:  $50.00 fine plus court costs including DNA sample/surcharge. 

COURT grants 2 days credit. 

DEOJ RH:  7/18/2023 at 9:00 a.m. 

Bond continues.  

Adj:  9:30 a.m.
